/-
We define the cyclic and i.i.d. learning efficiencies `cyclic_le` and `iid_le`. We prove that the i.i.d. learning efficiency with a uniform distribution is less than or equal to the cyclic learning efficiency (`cyclic_le_ge_iid_le_uniform`), which implies that there exists a task distribution (specifically the uniform one) that improves upon or matches the cyclic performance (`optimal_task_distribution_improves`). We also show that they are equal when the terms are non-zero (`commutative_cyclic_eq_iid_le_of_ne_zero`).
-/

